title: Excellent two stroke oil
description: I own A 1996 Nitro Bass boat, With a 1996 200 mariner Two stroke I have been using quicksilver oil 18 years In this motor 17 years ago My documented Psi in each cylinder That I wrote on scrap paper LOL Was 124,123,125,124,123,122.8. Since then As of last summer The compression only changed Slightly I still have 122, 123. I can tell you knock on wood My motor runs excellent I absolutely contribute  Using this oil Has something to do with it If you have an old boat as I do Motor. Are use There high performance synthetic blend Number 8M0078011 There's not a better oil on the market It's a little pricey But for the older motors It's the cats meow I'm seeing is believing kind a guy If it sucks I'm going to tell you In this case I would recommend it to anybody And all their two-stroke motor's.
